Thank you for registering for VMware vSphere Hypervisor, which includes VMware ESXi and 
vSphere Client.

Your license and download information can be found below.  If you have questions or need 
support, visit the VMware Technology Network [http://communities.vmware.com/community/vmtn]
for product documentation, knowledge bases and other resources, or contact your local 
authorized VMware partner. [http://www.vmware.com/partnerlocator/]  Additional support is 
also available for purchase within the VMware store. [http://www.vmware.com/go/buyesxserver3i]

The latest version of VMware vSphere Hypervisor is based on VMware ESXi 5.0 which is certified
to run on a broad range of 64-bit hardware.  Check the Hardware Compatibility List 
[http://www.vmware.com/resources/compatibility/search.php] to ensure that the server model you 
intend to use is certified to run VMware ESXi 5.0. For 32-bit hardware support, download the 
previous version of VMware vSphere Hypervisor, [https://www.vmware.com/go/getesxi/] which is 
based on VMware ESXi 3.5 and is supported on 32-bit hardware.



